        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A−4 The answer is no; indeed, S = Q\\ {n + 2/5|n ∈ Z} sat- isfies the given conditions. Clearly S satisfies (a) and (b); we need only check that it satisfies (c). It suffices to show that if x = p/q is a fraction with (p, q) = 1 and p > 0, then we cannot have 1/(x(x − 1)) = n + 2/5 for an integer n. Suppose otherwise; then",
        "bbox": [
