        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Write k(x) = f (x)g(x)h(x); then  = 6k2 + 6 andk(0) = 1. One solution for this differential equation with this initial condition is k(x) = tan(6x + π/4); by standard uniqueness, this must necessarily hold for x in some open interval around 0. Now the first given equation becomes",
        "bbox": [
