        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Remark. More generally, no rational number of the form m/n, where m, n are relatively prime and neither of ±m is a quadratic residue mod n, need be in S. If x = p/q is in lowest terms and 1/(x(x − 1)) = m/n + k for some integer k, then p(p − q) is relatively prime to q2; q2/(p(p − q)) = (m + kn) /n then implies that m + kn = ±q2 and so ±m must be a quadratic residue mod n.",
        "bbox": [
